reviews.title: Excellent app!
reviews.comment: The application gives you a great summary of your 401(k)
reviews.author: Edward Mullan

reviews.title: Meh
reviews.comment: Would be great if it wasn\'t super, ultra, mega slow dot org.
reviews.author: Justin Rinehuls

reviews.title: New to it
reviews.comment: I like it
reviews.author: Jason Sug

reviews.title: NOT ENOUGH!!
reviews.comment: I think the app needs some material from the Fidelity App, like weekly contributions made, more options in settings, a drag down refresh option. A option to change how much money we put into our benifits these are just a few sugetions!!!
reviews.author: Derrick Allen

reviews.title: Not good enough
reviews.comment: This app is just a slow clunky Web app packaged as an android app... Poor form, the customer deserves better
reviews.author: jason jones

reviews.title: View only?
reviews.comment: I did some perusing on the app and it appears that this is only for looking and not for transferring or performing any maintenance on a retirement account (my particular situation is for a company 401k account). Leaving out the ability to make changes to the accounts make this app almost pointless.
reviews.author: Jason Self

reviews.title: Horrible last update to an otherwise great app
reviews.comment: Everything looks misaligned on the S4.
reviews.author: Mikhail Krel

reviews.comment: Grt App.    Need space
reviews.author: Jeannette Wright

reviews.title: App has a \"log out\" option
reviews.comment: Just downloaded it today, and easily found the \"log out\" option in the top left corner. Then hit the home button on my phone and I was out. Looks good so far for version 1.0 Looking forward to future updates.
reviews.author: Warren Mitchell

reviews.title: Had to re-boot to exit!  UN-ACCEPTABLE!!
reviews.comment: Except for the Glaring error of not being able to get out of the Application, the program is well laid-out to clearly show you the current status of your NetBenefits.  You can not make any adjustments.  This is read only.  Fix the exit issue and you get a 4 star review.  Allow me to make changes to my portfolio, you will get a 5 star review.  I like your design and layout, easy to read and navigate.
reviews.author: Don Struble

reviews.title: Needs cosmetic work
reviews.comment: Needs more options.  A menu with an exit option, research, allocations, etc.  If you\'re going to make a mobile app, then make it more site-like if it\'s geared towards making it easier to stay on top of ones investments.
reviews.author: Gustavo Castellon

reviews.title: Cool app, but can\'t exit
reviews.comment: I realy enjoyed using the app.  I found it easy to navigate and useful.  I was able to logout without any problem.  The app put me back at the login screen, and I couldn\'t exit.  Each time I tried, I was back at the login screen.  App killer wouldn\'t kill it so I have to reboot after using this app.  This is a serikous bug.
reviews.author: Clayton Martin

reviews.title: C -minus
reviews.comment: Can\'t log out, also cannot find my health benefit info.....Nice Layout.
reviews.author: John doe

reviews.title: Seems good, but some issues
reviews.comment: I was happy to find this app, but I\'m having trouble backing out after I log out.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Good but
reviews.comment: Can\'t log out. Have to force stop it every time
reviews.author: Don A

reviews.title: Can\'t read numbers on my Nexus 7
reviews.comment: Fonts are too small, even with my glasses. The screen is filled with mostly blank space, yet the font that the numbers are displayed with are tiny.  No stretch/zoom function. Will wait for next version and uninstall if not fixed by then.
reviews.author: Ed Elias

reviews.title: No way to exit
reviews.comment: I like the app, but there is no way to exit the application. Please fix.
reviews.author: George Richard

reviews.comment: Would be fine if out could close without crashing
reviews.author: Mike Marlatt

reviews.title: Poor UI
reviews.comment: No daily gain/loss for total plan, daily gain/loss for individual funds is difficult to find.  Few options, shows you your allocation and not much else.
reviews.author: Kilty Monroe
